Shop Group Plans - www.westernhealth.com
































































PLAN OPTIONS FOR SMALL BUSINESS
 



TRADITIONAL
			PLANS
Traditional Plans are ideal for employees looking for the most coverage for their medical care. While many services are covered in full, others require only a copayment without the hassle of meeting a deductible first.




DEDUCTIBLE
			PLANS
Employees can control how much they spend on health care expenses by paying for services when needed. Office visits and/or diagnostic services require only a copayment while other services are subject to a deductible.




HSA-COMPATIBLE
			HIGH-DEDUCTIBLE PLANS
Employees get comprehensive health care with low monthly premiums. They can take advantage of tax-free savings and investments, while building funds within their HSA* to pay for office and hospital visits as well as prescription medications.



*An HSA-compatible high-deductible health plan with WHA can be paired with a Health Savings Account (HSA). While there is no obligation to have a HSA, you are advised to discuss the benefits with your tax consultant.

PLAN OPTIONS FOR LARGE BUSINESS    


 


Need help? We love to help!
Using a health insurance broker is the easiest, most efficient way to find health coverage. Western Health Advantage can help you find the broker who is right for your business.
A broker can help you:

Investigate and evaluate available health care plans and providers who offer you a wide range of health insurance options
Navigate legal and compliance issues, including the Health Insurance Portability and Accountability Act (HIPAA), the Consolidated Omnibus Budget Reconciliation Act (COBRA), the Employee Retirement Income Security Act (ERISA), and other regulations
Educate your employees about their new health coverage, including hosting employee benefit orientations

Health Insurance Agents and brokers make the task of finding the right benefit package for your employees and your bottom line – easy.
Put us to work for you!
If you would like more information about Western Health Advantage or assistance with finding a broker, please use the form on your right to provide us with some basic information about your business as well as your contact information.



       




